<wp_sync_dateCreated>20111110T02:10:17</wp_sync_dateCreated>

<wp_sync_description>We are proud to highlight <a href="http://twitter.com/chkal">Christian Kaltepoth</a>, who gave a fabulous presentation on [[PrettyFaces]] at <a href="http://jax.de">WJAX/JAXCon</a> in Munich on Wednesday, November 10th - 2011. Christan presented with <a href="http://twitter.com/andybosch">Andy Bosch</a>, who gave a short intro of URL-rewriting, what it means for applications in general, and why you should do URL-rewriting.

<div class="featured" style="margin-top: 15px;">
<table cellspacing="10px"><tr><td>
<img src="http://ocpsoft.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/444495465-300x225.jpg" align="left" alt="" title="christian-presenting" width="300" height="225" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2861" style="float: left; margin: 15px;" />
Key points include:
<ul>
	<li>URL-rewriting can be used to create human-readable URLs, which is good for user-experience.</li>
	<li>REST-ful URLs using keywords benefit search engine optimization (SEO)</li>
	<li>Hiding non-essential URL information such as page extensions (.jsp, .xhtml, .do) helps protect your applications from vulnerability.</li>	
	<li>With URL-rewriting, REST-ful URLs can be applied to any new or existing application</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
</table>
</div></wp_sync_description>

<wp_sync_link>http://ocpsoft.org/prettyfaces/prettyfaces-at-jaxcon-munich/</wp_sync_link>

